parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden collapse of the driver's seat backrest can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The driver's seat backrest suddenly falls backward
the seat does not lock or relatch in place
the seat is stuck in a reclined position
the seat is broken and cannot be adjusted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper electric module can cause the windshield wipers to malfunction or not operate at all, reducing visibility during inclement weather and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Windshield wipers intermittently fail during operation
windshield wipers will not come on at all
inconsistent or erratic windshield wiper performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) in wet weather can cause the vehicle's brakes to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes lock up when applying the ABS brakes in wet weather
the vehicle surges forward after brake release
and the stopping distance is increased.
